Call By Value
Call By Reference

Both Call by Value [setter method] and CAll by Reference[normal method with obj as parameter] is
used for updating an existing object

Call by Value is used to update one value of the object at a time
Call by Reference is used to update multiple value of an object at a time

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CRUD: Create[setter/constructor], Retrieve[getter method], Update[setter/CBR], Delete
While making variable, think

should we make it global - if its value has to be shared by multiple methods of the same class
should we pass it as parameter - if its value is not to be shared with other methods of the same class
should we make it local - if the value will remain same/fixed where ever this is needed and can't be changed


If the global variable is holding sensitive data, as per encapsulation, we should make it private
now, if we make this private, i cannot access it and set its value
so now to set the value of private variable we have 2 options
 1. constructor [if these variables are mandatory]
 2. setter method[if these variables are non-mandatory]

If i have to update the value of these variables, we have 2 options
 1. Call by value [using setter method to update one value at a time]
 2. Call by reference [create method with object as parameter, to update multiple values ar a time]

